JDBC(Java Database Connectivity)
# there are four types of drivers

# To connect java to database we need 7 steps
    1) import the package ( java.Sql.*)
    2) load and register the driver ( load the driver + register the driver)
            driver for particular database like mysql , oracle etc
            driver for mysql is "com.mysql.jdbc.driver"
            forName is a method to load and register we have to pass string driver it
            belong to class name Class
    3) establish the connection - to connect we have to instantiate interface-
        connection
    4) create the statement
        statement , prepare statement , callable statement
    5) execute the query
    6) process result
    7) close